    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1888-05-31T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1888-05-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="500" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d500">
                <head>No. 45.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Garland</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Bayard</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of Justice</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1888-05-31">
                            <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 31, 1888</date>.
                                (Received June 1.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of your letter of the 29th instant, inclosing a copy of a
                            memorandum from the British minister, in relation to the cases of
                            seizure of British vessels in Behring Sea, and to say that I know of no
                            mode remaining by which the decrees of condemnation can be reviewed.</p>
                <p>Very respectfully,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">A. H. Garland.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
